1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,794
[Erica] <i>Your mother</i>
<i>has a deep grudge against me.</i>

2
00:00:02,877 --> 00:00:04,671
<i>She has never been a real mother to me.</i>

3
00:00:04,754 --> 00:00:06,589
<i>Whatever relationship</i>
<i>I had with your mother before</i>

4
00:00:06,673 --> 00:00:07,841
<i>has long been over.</i>

5
00:00:10,135 --> 00:00:12,387
<i>What happened? It's not me!</i> [sobbing]

6
00:00:12,470 --> 00:00:14,764
[Alice] <i>We all know who did this.</i>

7
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:15,849
<i>Good girl.</i>

8
00:00:15,932 --> 00:00:17,892
<i>After this scandal,</i>

9
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:20,145
<i>who do you think will still love me?</i>

10
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:22,105
[Alice] <i>Many people will still love you.</i>

11
00:00:22,188 --> 00:00:23,356
<i>So many of us love you.</i>

12
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:27,277
<i>Now, I've finally set</i>
<i>these videos and myself free.</i>

13
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:29,237
<i>- It's done.</i>
<i>- I'm so proud of you.</i>

14
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:31,489
<i>Mr. Montenegro,</i>
<i>the family court requires you</i>

15
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:32,866
<i>to leave this house immediately.</i>

16
00:00:32,949 --> 00:00:34,284
<i>You're fucking useless!</i>

17
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:37,078
<i>Dear, I have something to tell you.</i>
<i>You have to know that…</i>

18
00:00:37,162 --> 00:00:38,246
[school bell rings]

19
00:00:38,329 --> 00:00:39,414
<i>Go ahead, Ma. Carry on.</i>

20
00:00:39,497 --> 00:00:41,249
<i>It's okay. Let's just continue this later.</i>

21
00:00:41,332 --> 00:00:42,584
<i>Are you really okay with us leaving?</i>

22
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:43,752
<i>We have to protect Seth.</i>

23
00:00:43,835 --> 00:00:45,545
<i>I always want to remember her.</i>

24
00:00:45,628 --> 00:00:47,130
<i>She's still my favorite.</i>

25
00:00:47,213 --> 00:00:49,340
<i>Sir, I beg you. I need protection!</i>

26
00:00:49,424 --> 00:00:51,718
<i>Okay. That's if</i>
<i>you give us good information.</i>

27
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:53,511
<i>Lost beauty queens.</i>

28
00:00:53,595 --> 00:00:56,139
<i>For three months,</i>
<i>she was beaten up and raped repeatedly.</i>

29
00:00:56,222 --> 00:00:57,557
<i>Do you really think she'll be at peace</i>

30
00:00:57,640 --> 00:01:00,810
<i>knowing that the man</i>
<i>who violated her is not in jail?</i>

31
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:02,395
<i>But this is what we need to do!</i>

32
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:05,190
[Alice]<i> He intentionally</i>
<i>buried Esther here to rub it in our face</i>

33
00:01:05,273 --> 00:01:08,651
<i>that he wouldn't let our dream</i>
<i>of growing old together come true!</i>

34
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,904
<i>- Uncle Edward? Auntie Christina?</i>
<i>- Help me.</i>

35
00:01:10,987 --> 00:01:13,323
<i>What happened?</i>
<i>Aunty Christina, where's Edward?</i>

36
00:01:17,452 --> 00:01:24,167
[theme music playing]

37
00:02:32,861 --> 00:02:34,362
[voice prompt]
<i>The subscriber cannot be reached.</i>

38
00:02:34,445 --> 00:02:35,822
<i>Please try again later.</i>

39
00:02:35,905 --> 00:02:37,407
She's still not answering.

40
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:38,366
[sighs]

41
00:02:38,449 --> 00:02:42,704
Didn't I tell
you to keep an eye on Althea?

42
00:02:42,787 --> 00:02:44,956
I shouldn't have let her go with you!

43
00:02:45,498 --> 00:02:48,042
You said you'd keep an eye on her!

44
00:02:48,376 --> 00:02:49,919
[Frank] What was I supposed to do?

45
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:53,214
While the electric fan was being fixed,

46
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:56,885
she asked for my
permission to go to the store nearby.

47
00:02:56,968 --> 00:02:58,261
She said she'd be right back.

48
00:02:58,344 --> 00:03:00,513
Why did you give her permission?

49
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:03,600
You know that Edong
is just lurking around, right?

50
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:05,310
Even if there were many people around,

51
00:03:05,393 --> 00:03:08,438
he could've easily
taken our daughter! [sobbing]

52
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:10,899
What if he already has Althea?

53
00:03:10,982 --> 00:03:14,068
What if something bad
has already happened to her?

54
00:03:14,152 --> 00:03:15,153
[knocks on door]

55
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:21,868
[ominous music playing]

56
00:03:21,951 --> 00:03:24,329
- [door creaks]
- Were you able to contact Althea?

57
00:03:24,412 --> 00:03:26,623
We still can't reach her.

58
00:03:27,624 --> 00:03:28,958
I'm begging you.

59
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:32,503
Maybe we can inform the police now
that Althea is missing.

60
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:34,464
What if that monster
has already taken her?

61
00:03:34,547 --> 00:03:36,758
What if something bad has happened to her?
What if she's been raped?

62
00:03:36,841 --> 00:03:37,884
Edong is not a rapist.

63
00:03:38,301 --> 00:03:40,094
That's not his modus operandi.

64
00:03:40,511 --> 00:03:41,971
All men…

65
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:43,973
if given the chance, can be rapists!

66
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:45,475
[Althea] Ma!

67
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:48,436
- [Althea] Erica.
- Althea?

68
00:03:48,519 --> 00:03:49,562
Althea!

69
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:51,105
Seriously? Where have you been?

70
00:03:51,189 --> 00:03:52,690
We've been looking for you!

71
00:03:52,774 --> 00:03:54,651
Your father and I were very worried!

72
00:03:54,734 --> 00:03:56,110
I sent a text message to Papa

73
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:58,488
saying that I'd drop
by Uncle Edward's house

74
00:03:58,571 --> 00:04:00,156
since it was near the repair shop.

75
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,282
[Frank] A text message?

76
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:03,618
We didn't receive any
text message from you.

77
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:06,162
We tried calling you multiple times,

78
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:08,039
but you didn't answer.

79
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:11,209
I'm sorry, my phone battery died.

80
00:04:11,292 --> 00:04:13,086
Why did you go there
alone in the first place?

81
00:04:13,586 --> 00:04:16,297
That's where Edong attacked you, remember?

82
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:20,260
Because I heard…

83
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:23,763
a body was found buried
at Uncle Edward's old house.

84
00:04:24,472 --> 00:04:25,640
A corpse?

85
00:04:25,723 --> 00:04:28,559
It was identified to be Esther Castro,

86
00:04:28,643 --> 00:04:30,728
the first witness to incriminate Edong.

87
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:33,356
We were on our way there when you called.

88
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:37,277
Ma, I was just worried about Uncle Edward.

89
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:40,905
I know he and
Auntie Christina loved that house so much.

90
00:04:40,989 --> 00:04:44,033
I thought they'd be
greatly affected by the news,

91
00:04:44,117 --> 00:04:45,827
so I decided to check on them.

92
00:04:48,037 --> 00:04:49,122
[Althea gasps]

93
00:04:51,374 --> 00:04:57,547
[sinister music playing]

94
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:06,848
[music fades]

95
00:05:06,931 --> 00:05:08,850
<i>- Althea.</i>
<i>- Uncle Edward!</i>

96
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:11,144
<i>You startled me!</i>

97
00:05:11,602 --> 00:05:12,687
[relieved sigh]

98
00:05:12,770 --> 00:05:14,856
<i>I thought you were Edong because…</i>

99
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:17,608
<i>this is where he attacked me.</i>

100
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:20,737
<i>Sorry about that, Althea.</i>

101
00:05:21,863 --> 00:05:23,364
<i>But you startled me, too.</i>

102
00:05:23,448 --> 00:05:26,159
[breathy chuckle] <i>Sorry, Uncle.</i>

103
00:05:27,243 --> 00:05:30,830
<i>I just came here because I heard about…</i>

104
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:33,082
<i>…the body.</i>

105
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:34,834
<i>Have you heard about it?</i>

106
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:38,129
<i>A body was found</i>
<i>buried in front of your old house.</i>

107
00:05:38,212 --> 00:05:41,049
[uneasy music playing]

108
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:42,341
<i>Ah, yes.</i>

109
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:44,719
<i>I went there to see.</i>

110
00:05:46,262 --> 00:05:47,889
<i>I can't believe it.</i>

111
00:05:49,974 --> 00:05:52,226
[Althea] Uncle Edward
was very much affected.

112
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:56,939
I already called Alice to let her know.

113
00:05:57,023 --> 00:06:00,193
[uneasy music continues]

114
00:06:00,276 --> 00:06:04,572
Ma, Pa, I'm so sorry for making you worry.

115
00:06:04,655 --> 00:06:07,116
My goodness, Althea! Don't do that again!

116
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:10,286
What good would your apology
do if you were killed or raped?!

117
00:06:11,245 --> 00:06:12,914
[Althea] I'm really sorry, Ma.

118
00:06:12,997 --> 00:06:14,290
I won't do it again.

119
00:06:14,373 --> 00:06:19,170
[uneasy music continues]

120
00:06:27,178 --> 00:06:29,013
[music fades]

121
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:33,059
I can't believe
he defiled that house, Alice!

122
00:06:39,982 --> 00:06:41,526
That's your house now.

123
00:06:42,026 --> 00:06:44,779
And I know how
special it is to you and your friends.

124
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:48,741
[both huff]

125
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:54,330
Have I told
you that that was my first home?

126
00:06:55,123 --> 00:06:57,375
That's where I grew up.

127
00:06:58,334 --> 00:06:59,627
It was my father's.

128
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:04,298
But…

129
00:07:10,471 --> 00:07:12,432
I didn't have good memories there.

130
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:16,853
[eerie music playing]

131
00:07:16,936 --> 00:07:18,771
Have I told you, Alice…

132
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:22,984
how my father would hurt me?

133
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:27,405
[young boy crying]

134
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:29,615
People thought…

135
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:32,910
my father was a saint.

136
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:34,579
[Edward's father] <i>You're no different!</i>

137
00:07:34,662 --> 00:07:36,164
<i>You'll turn out just as bad as me!</i>

138
00:07:36,247 --> 00:07:38,332
- But he wasn't.
- [boy continues crying]

139
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,294
He was far from a saint.

140
00:07:41,377 --> 00:07:45,673
[eerie music continues]

141
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:47,508
So, when he died,

142
00:07:49,385 --> 00:07:51,053
I had that house demolished.

143
00:07:53,931 --> 00:07:55,683
And I built a new one.

144
00:07:55,766 --> 00:07:59,562
[eerie music continues]

145
00:07:59,645 --> 00:08:01,063
With Christina.

146
00:08:03,649 --> 00:08:05,193
And I made sure that…

147
00:08:07,361 --> 00:08:09,322
that house would be filled…

148
00:08:10,781 --> 00:08:12,783
with happy memories.

149
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:18,831
That's why I couldn't sell it.

150
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:21,959
Until you bought it.

151
00:08:22,418 --> 00:08:23,544
You were the exception, Alice.

152
00:08:25,671 --> 00:08:29,425
I didn't know you went through all that.

153
00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:35,097
You didn't tell Papa?

154
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:39,519
[eerie music continues]

155
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:42,522
I wish you would have told him.

156
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:45,566
I'm sure he would have listened to you.

157
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:49,779
I was scared of my father.

158
00:08:51,405 --> 00:08:53,241
And I didn't want
Mike to get dragged into it.

159
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:57,036
[Edward sniffles]

160
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:03,834
[music fades]

161
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:05,336
[Edward sobs]

162
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:14,053
[unsettling music playing]

163
00:09:28,609 --> 00:09:30,236
- I'm glad nothing bad happened to Althea.
- [music fades]

164
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:32,488
Where should we go now?

165
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:34,740
To Alice or the police station?

166
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:36,659
[tense music playing]

167
00:09:36,742 --> 00:09:38,119
[Annette] <i>Althea?!</i>

168
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:40,204
<i>Sweetie, what happened?!</i>

169
00:09:40,663 --> 00:09:42,748
<i>What did he do to you? Did he touch you?</i>

170
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:44,834
<i>I'm begging you.</i>

171
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:47,962
<i>Maybe we can inform the police now</i>
<i>that Althea is missing.</i>

172
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:49,797
<i>What if that monster</i>
<i>has already taken her?</i>

173
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:52,091
<i>What if something bad has happened to her?</i>
<i>What if she's been raped?</i>

174
00:09:53,968 --> 00:09:56,220
[young Erica] <i>My father</i>
<i>was the one who left you.</i>

175
00:09:56,304 --> 00:09:58,472
<i>He was the one who wronged you. Not me.</i>

176
00:09:58,556 --> 00:10:00,725
<i>But why did you punish me too?</i>

177
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:03,769
<i>You didn't treat me as</i>
<i>your daughter even once.</i>

178
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:05,980
<i>You look so much like him.</i>

179
00:10:06,063 --> 00:10:08,649
[tense music swells]

180
00:10:09,525 --> 00:10:11,444
What? Hey!

181
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:14,655
[music fades]

182
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:17,742
Are you a rape victim?

183
00:10:25,082 --> 00:10:26,417
What are you saying?

184
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:30,713
Did you get pregnant
because you were raped?

185
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:36,010
Get out.

186
00:10:38,971 --> 00:10:40,556
Answer my question.

187
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:44,518
Is it me?

188
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:47,730
[somber music playing]

189
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:49,231
Was I the result of that?

190
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:55,821
Am I the daughter of your rapist?

191
00:10:55,905 --> 00:11:00,993
[somber music continues]

192
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:05,164
Yes…

193
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:10,961
[Annette sniffles, cries]

194
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:14,340
I was studying in another province.

195
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:19,011
I thought he loved me.

196
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:23,599
He made me believe it…

197
00:11:23,682 --> 00:11:26,811
[somber music continues]

198
00:11:26,894 --> 00:11:30,481
[sniffles] He asked me out, one night.

199
00:11:31,774 --> 00:11:34,485
[sobbing] I was so happy.

200
00:11:36,570 --> 00:11:39,490
Until he forced himself on me.

201
00:11:39,573 --> 00:11:41,951
[music becomes uneasy]

202
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:44,829
I said I didn't want to do it! [crying]

203
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:49,125
I kept telling him, "no."

204
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:54,004
I kept pleading! [crying]

205
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:56,215
"Stop it!"

206
00:11:56,298 --> 00:12:00,052
[crying]

207
00:12:00,136 --> 00:12:02,096
"Stop it…"

208
00:12:02,179 --> 00:12:06,142
[uneasy music continues]

209
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:08,060
[breathes shakily]

210
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:11,480
I didn't report it to the police.

211
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:17,361
Because my father said
I should just marry him instead.

212
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:23,075
How could I marry the man who raped me?!

213
00:12:26,745 --> 00:12:28,164
So, I ran away…

214
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:31,709
I came here to Amurao.

215
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:36,046
And then I found out I was pregnant.

216
00:12:36,839 --> 00:12:39,175
[sobs] I wanted to terminate it!

217
00:12:39,258 --> 00:12:43,429
[uneasy music continues]

218
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:48,184
I didn't want that child to become a stain
in this world, just like their father.

219
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:52,229
[somber music resumes]

220
00:12:52,313 --> 00:12:54,440
I decided to abort the child.

221
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:58,694
But I couldn't do it…[crying]

222
00:13:01,238 --> 00:13:03,032
I couldn't kill that child.

223
00:13:03,115 --> 00:13:07,161
[somber music continues]

224
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:09,246
"You look so much like him."

225
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,585
That's what you told me.

226
00:13:16,795 --> 00:13:19,340
[Annette sobbing]

227
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:21,050
Even just once…

228
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:23,719
Did you ever looked at me…

229
00:13:25,012 --> 00:13:27,014
without seeing his face?

230
00:13:27,097 --> 00:13:31,018
[somber music continues]

231
00:13:31,101 --> 00:13:33,854
Did you really see me?

232
00:13:35,439 --> 00:13:38,651
Or did you just
pray that I stop breathing?

233
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:45,533
[somber music continues]

234
00:13:45,616 --> 00:13:48,452
You may not have aborted me…

235
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:52,248
[sniffles]

236
00:13:52,331 --> 00:13:55,918
But each day
that you regretted that decision…

237
00:13:58,003 --> 00:14:00,756
You killed me over and over again!

238
00:14:00,839 --> 00:14:02,925
[both crying]

239
00:14:03,008 --> 00:14:04,635
Again and again!

240
00:14:06,387 --> 00:14:10,015
[sobbing]

241
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:18,649
[sobbing, breathing heavily]

242
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:29,743
[somber music continues]

243
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:33,789
[crying]

244
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:36,417
[sobs]

245
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:42,673
[crying]

246
00:14:46,427 --> 00:14:51,265
[sniffling, crying]

247
00:14:53,475 --> 00:14:54,852
[sniffling]

248
00:14:57,396 --> 00:15:02,693
[Erica sniffling]

249
00:15:02,776 --> 00:15:03,861
I'm okay.

250
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:06,071
I'm okay.

251
00:15:08,157 --> 00:15:12,828
[Erica sniffling, crying]

252
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:17,958
[plates clanging]

253
00:15:19,668 --> 00:15:22,129
[music fades]

254
00:15:22,212 --> 00:15:25,049
[sniffles] Ma, why didn't you tell me?

255
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:29,970
Because I already
tried to forget all of those.

256
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:37,144
Remembering all that won't help our lives.

257
00:15:38,854 --> 00:15:42,524
[Althea] When you didn't say it,
did that help you?

258
00:15:43,651 --> 00:15:45,152
Or even my sister?

259
00:15:46,403 --> 00:15:47,404
Althea.

260
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:50,491
Your mother went through a difficult time.

261
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,284
I know!

262
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:54,495
I know that.

263
00:15:55,746 --> 00:15:57,206
[breathes sharply]

264
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:58,374
But, Ma…

265
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:01,043
Erica is innocent.

266
00:16:01,126 --> 00:16:03,212
[cries]

267
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:04,463
I know.

268
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:08,175
[crying]

269
00:16:09,677 --> 00:16:12,179
I admitted that to you, didn't I?

270
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:15,849
That I wished that wasn't my reaction.

271
00:16:16,517 --> 00:16:18,519
That I wished I was strong enough.

272
00:16:19,770 --> 00:16:22,815
[cries] That I wished I didn't let
my anger get the best of me,

273
00:16:22,898 --> 00:16:25,985
that I wished I were a good mother to her.

274
00:16:26,068 --> 00:16:28,028
[somber music resumes]

275
00:16:28,112 --> 00:16:31,031
But I can't change what happened.

276
00:16:32,408 --> 00:16:36,286
I can't take back
everything I said and did to Erica…

277
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:41,834
I'll carry that until my last breath.

278
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:47,339
[poignant music playing]

279
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:50,175
[sobs] That's my burden.

280
00:16:53,053 --> 00:16:57,433
[poignant music continues]

281
00:16:57,516 --> 00:17:00,185
[crying]

282
00:17:05,107 --> 00:17:06,400
- [door shuts]
- [music fades]

283
00:17:17,995 --> 00:17:18,954
[bottle thuds]

284
00:17:19,788 --> 00:17:22,332
- You need another?
- No, I'm okay.

285
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:27,087
You know, you don't
have to be okay right away.

286
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:30,883
Just let yourself feel what you feel.

287
00:17:33,343 --> 00:17:34,720
It won't change anything.

288
00:17:37,014 --> 00:17:37,890
[Erica sniffles]

289
00:17:38,348 --> 00:17:39,850
It just explained why…

290
00:17:41,643 --> 00:17:42,978
my mother is like that.

291
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,940
[melancholic music playing]

292
00:17:47,024 --> 00:17:48,650
Back then, I couldn't understand…

293
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:52,404
why she was so mad at me.

294
00:17:58,327 --> 00:17:59,620
But now, I know.

295
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:05,209
But that won't change my life.

296
00:18:05,292 --> 00:18:08,462
[melancholic music continues]

297
00:18:08,545 --> 00:18:10,297
I've already built a life,

298
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:14,843
away from her and her history.

299
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:19,473
[melancholic music continues]

300
00:18:19,556 --> 00:18:20,641
But?

301
00:18:25,062 --> 00:18:26,480
I was just in shock earlier.

302
00:18:28,023 --> 00:18:29,274
But I'm fine now.

303
00:18:31,401 --> 00:18:32,778
[music fades]

304
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:36,865
[Chloe] Ma! Is it true that Miss Esther

305
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:40,285
was one of
the witnesses who imprisoned Edong

306
00:18:40,369 --> 00:18:42,246
for Louisa's murder?

307
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:45,040
Yeah…

308
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:50,170
[plastic bag rustles]

309
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:51,338
But…

310
00:18:53,715 --> 00:18:55,759
But Esther lied.

311
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:59,596
It wasn't Edong whom she saw that night.

312
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:03,267
So…

313
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:06,645
Her statement was fake?

314
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:08,355
Why's that?

315
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:15,112
Um…

316
00:19:15,195 --> 00:19:18,490
At the time, Esther had a lot of money.

317
00:19:19,032 --> 00:19:22,035
It came from her alumni batch.

318
00:19:22,911 --> 00:19:25,956
She said she lost
it in a pickpocket incident.

319
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:27,791
But…

320
00:19:29,293 --> 00:19:31,128
Edong knew that wasn't true.

321
00:19:32,337 --> 00:19:33,672
So…

322
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:36,466
She put Edong in jail,
so she wouldn't go to jail.

323
00:19:40,762 --> 00:19:41,930
Sheesh!

324
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:44,683
If there are people who need a reminder

325
00:19:44,766 --> 00:19:47,311
that nothing good happens from lying,

326
00:19:48,312 --> 00:19:50,355
they should just look at Miss Esther.

327
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:52,608
<i>Liar!</i>

328
00:19:52,691 --> 00:19:55,986
[Lucas]<i>You Beth, were the first to lie!</i>

329
00:19:56,069 --> 00:19:57,571
<i>You're the one who started this!</i>

330
00:19:57,654 --> 00:20:01,533
[uneasy music playing

331
00:20:01,617 --> 00:20:03,493
- [sighs heavily]
- [music fades]

332
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:06,330
Chloe…

333
00:20:06,955 --> 00:20:11,877
Can we continue
our "to be continued" conversation?

334
00:20:13,795 --> 00:20:15,297
What is it, Ma?

335
00:20:15,714 --> 00:20:17,382
Why do you look so serious?

336
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:20,135
- Sit down.
- [chair scrapes]

337
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:29,686
[Beth exhales heavily]

338
00:20:31,104 --> 00:20:35,317
Do you remember Miss Esther?

339
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:39,112
The one from our testimony back then,

340
00:20:39,196 --> 00:20:41,490
the one who helped get Edong jailed?

341
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:46,578
The police found a watch back then

342
00:20:46,662 --> 00:20:48,664
in the stolen items Edong had.

343
00:20:49,456 --> 00:20:51,583
And we said it was Louisa's watch.

344
00:20:54,795 --> 00:20:56,046
But the truth is…

345
00:20:58,799 --> 00:21:00,008
that watch didn't belong to Louisa.

346
00:21:00,092 --> 00:21:02,135
["Sabay Sabay Tayo"
somber instrumental playing]

347
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:03,345
What?

348
00:21:03,428 --> 00:21:04,972
[Chloe breath quivers]

349
00:21:05,389 --> 00:21:06,932
I don’t understand.

350
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:09,935
Louisa's watch…

351
00:21:10,852 --> 00:21:14,231
had an "L" engraved on the back.

352
00:21:16,149 --> 00:21:18,485
But the one the police found…

353
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:23,782
The watch looked exactly like Louisa's,

354
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:28,370
but it didn't have an "L" on the back.

355
00:21:31,999 --> 00:21:33,625
It wasn’t hers.

356
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:36,670
<i>Yes.</i>

357
00:21:37,546 --> 00:21:40,299
But I told the police it was hers.

358
00:21:40,382 --> 00:21:44,011
["Sabay Sabay Tayo"
somber instrumental continues]

359
00:21:44,094 --> 00:21:45,178
Ma…

360
00:21:47,681 --> 00:21:49,558
You lied?

361
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:54,646
[sobs softly]

362
00:21:56,898 --> 00:21:59,484
Yes. [breath hitches]

363
00:22:02,154 --> 00:22:04,364
I lied.

364
00:22:06,575 --> 00:22:09,536
[sobbing softly]

365
00:22:11,079 --> 00:22:14,041
Ma…is this a prank?

366
00:22:14,124 --> 00:22:15,709
Is this your prank?

367
00:22:15,792 --> 00:22:17,836
How could you do that, Ma?

368
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:19,963
You, of all people?

369
00:22:21,256 --> 00:22:22,966
Back then, I thought…

370
00:22:24,134 --> 00:22:25,594
that was what I had to do

371
00:22:25,677 --> 00:22:28,055
to put the one
who killed Louisa behind bars.

372
00:22:29,347 --> 00:22:30,766
[Chloe hesitates] S- So…

373
00:22:31,808 --> 00:22:35,729
W- What about Aunt Alice and the others?

374
00:22:37,314 --> 00:22:40,108
After I claimed it was Louisa's watch,

375
00:22:41,568 --> 00:22:43,320
they went along with it.

376
00:22:44,571 --> 00:22:47,157
That's what they told the police too.

377
00:22:47,991 --> 00:22:51,953
Aunt Alice at Aunt Mel?

378
00:22:55,916 --> 00:22:57,667
But not Aunt Erica.

379
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:04,257
[tense music playing]

380
00:23:04,341 --> 00:23:06,051
Is that why you fought, Ma?

381
00:23:06,843 --> 00:23:07,886
Is that why…

382
00:23:08,804 --> 00:23:11,765
By the time you graduated high school,

383
00:23:11,848 --> 00:23:15,435
you were only friends
with Aunt Mel and Aunt Alice?

384
00:23:15,519 --> 00:23:21,066
[tense music continues]

385
00:23:21,149 --> 00:23:22,067
[sniffles]

386
00:23:23,735 --> 00:23:25,445
[sniffling, sobbing]

387
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:29,783
But, sweetheart, you have to understand…

388
00:23:29,866 --> 00:23:34,663
Everyone was pressuring
us to say Edong killed Louisa.

389
00:23:34,746 --> 00:23:38,792
The police, Louisa's family,

390
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:41,670
the whole town of Amurao, everyone.

391
00:23:41,753 --> 00:23:44,422
That's what they believed.

392
00:23:45,340 --> 00:23:46,341
So,

393
00:23:46,842 --> 00:23:49,553
that's what we believed too.

394
00:23:50,846 --> 00:23:53,140
Sweetheart,
everyone was terrified back then.

395
00:23:54,057 --> 00:23:55,892
Everyone was exhausted…

396
00:23:57,352 --> 00:23:59,312
so I ended it.

397
00:23:59,729 --> 00:24:02,774
I told them
everything they wanted to hear.

398
00:24:02,858 --> 00:24:05,068
Even though it wasn't true!

399
00:24:05,152 --> 00:24:09,865
["Sabay Sabay Tayo"
instrumental continues]

400
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:11,032
Chloe…

401
00:24:13,535 --> 00:24:14,911
[sniffles]

402
00:24:14,995 --> 00:24:16,079
Chloe, please…

403
00:24:17,289 --> 00:24:21,334
You have to understand.
I'm telling you this because…

404
00:24:21,418 --> 00:24:23,420
[Chloe sniffling]

405
00:24:23,503 --> 00:24:25,589
…I was just a kid back then.

406
00:24:25,672 --> 00:24:28,466
I was only a few
years older than you back then.

407
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:32,512
It's easy to judge when
you weren't in that situation.

408
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:35,015
But you're the one who taught me, Mom!

409
00:24:35,765 --> 00:24:37,184
You taught me to

410
00:24:37,267 --> 00:24:39,269
never tolerate people
who take advantage of others,

411
00:24:39,352 --> 00:24:43,356
liars, and corrupt government officials.

412
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:47,527
So now I'm just as bad
as those corrupt people?

413
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:50,405
That's not what I'm saying, Ma!

414
00:24:50,488 --> 00:24:54,075
But someone went
to prison because you lied.

415
00:24:54,159 --> 00:24:58,079
Prison, Ma! His whole life!

416
00:24:58,830 --> 00:25:02,125
And if it's true
that he didn't kill your friend, Ma…

417
00:25:03,251 --> 00:25:05,212
Even if it's complicated…

418
00:25:05,712 --> 00:25:08,465
That was wrong, Ma. That was wrong!

419
00:25:09,966 --> 00:25:12,260
How were you able to…

420
00:25:14,888 --> 00:25:17,891
[Chloe sobbing, sniffling]

421
00:25:19,559 --> 00:25:21,895
I just can't picture it, Ma…

422
00:25:24,648 --> 00:25:30,570
I can't imagine
you doing that in any universe.

423
00:25:33,698 --> 00:25:34,991
I'm sorry.

424
00:25:37,327 --> 00:25:40,872
[sniffles]

425
00:25:42,374 --> 00:25:48,046
- [sobbing]
- [poignant music playing]

426
00:26:00,976 --> 00:26:02,644
[music fades]

427
00:26:02,727 --> 00:26:04,813
So, they've confirmed it?

428
00:26:04,896 --> 00:26:05,855
It's Esther?

429
00:26:06,398 --> 00:26:07,315
[Erica] Yes.

430
00:26:07,399 --> 00:26:09,276
[Mel] So what you're saying is…

431
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:12,237
Edong brought Esther's
body all the way to Amurao

432
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:13,822
just to bury it at our house?

433
00:26:15,073 --> 00:26:16,700
He’s that angry at us.

434
00:26:16,783 --> 00:26:19,869
He has to desecrate
whatever's important to us.

435
00:26:21,121 --> 00:26:24,249
The message is clear, he's not done yet.

436
00:26:24,791 --> 00:26:27,794
So we really have no
idea where he’s hiding?

437
00:26:29,713 --> 00:26:30,839
Not yet.

438
00:26:30,922 --> 00:26:33,216
But the police are still
searching for him nonstop.

439
00:26:33,300 --> 00:26:38,305
[phone ringing]

440
00:26:39,431 --> 00:26:41,891
[ringing continues]

441
00:26:41,975 --> 00:26:46,813
[foreboding music playing]

442
00:26:58,908 --> 00:27:01,619
I can tell you're all worked up in there.

443
00:27:03,204 --> 00:27:05,832
Hope you liked my gift.

444
00:27:05,915 --> 00:27:10,587
[foreboding music continues]

445
00:27:10,670 --> 00:27:12,839
You think you can ruin me?

446
00:27:13,798 --> 00:27:15,800
You can't destroy me, Mel.

447
00:27:15,884 --> 00:27:17,802
[chuckles darkly]

448
00:27:17,886 --> 00:27:19,637
You'll go down first.

449
00:27:22,974 --> 00:27:28,521
[foreboding music continues]

450
00:27:53,797 --> 00:27:57,092
[foreboding music crescendos]

451
00:27:58,009 --> 00:28:01,137
<i>You'll end up just like your father,</i>
<i>you monster!</i>

452
00:28:01,221 --> 00:28:05,767
[Alice] <i>Are there things</i>
<i>you think would be better off forgotten?</i>

453
00:28:05,850 --> 00:28:07,894
<i>Things that shouldn't resurface?</i>

454
00:28:07,977 --> 00:28:09,771
<i>I don't like your wife.</i>

455
00:28:09,854 --> 00:28:11,231
<i>You know what's a great idea?</i>

456
00:28:11,314 --> 00:28:13,691
<i>Let's team up. We can work together.</i>

457
00:28:13,775 --> 00:28:15,902
<i>I can also hurt her friends.</i>

458
00:28:19,531 --> 00:28:20,990
[shuddering] <i>Aah! Aah! Aah!</i>

459
00:28:21,074 --> 00:28:24,244
[both laughing menacingly]
